r ways to stay active as they age.";i:14;s:83:"Sit comfortable at the edge of your chair with both feet resting flat on the floor.";i:15;s:33:"Outstretch both arms to the side.";i:16;s:83:"Bring your arms together in front of your chest while slightly bending your elbows.";i:17;s:46:"Hold a sock hop or a Woodstock with 60s music.";i:18;s:71:"You could even choose a theme and choose songs from any genre that fit.";i:19;s:142:"For example a Blue Dance where you play songs like Blue Moon Blue Suede Shoes Blue Bayou and Blue Hawaii Look to the calendar for music ideas.";i:20;s:329:"This entry was posted in Senior Activities and tagged active seniors activity director assisted living games for seniors memory care national physical therapy month notjustbingo nursing facility nursing home retirement home senior activities senior center senior exercise senior facility senior residents target games toss games.";i:21;s:15:"Hook Loop Toss.";i:22;s:111:"Set up a hook and loop target for residents to play a game of tar grip toss where the balls stay on the target.";i:23;s:131:"For each round of the game have residents toss their tar grip balls to see who can land theirs closest to the center of the target.";i:24;s:278:"All exercises are goodwe do them allI was a dancer play the Pianothe sitting on chairs go down wellhold legs up point toes down then updown upwhile legs are up twist ankles round round each wayGentlyslowly raise arms up in front while breathing IN lowering arms down Out4 times.";i:25;s:104:"Repeat to breathing IN then move arms out to the sides holding the breathbreathing out with arms coming.";i:26;s:205:"Ask them to press the feet into the ground as they bring the nose over the knees and lift the buttocks just slightly off the chair or attempt to lift them off the chair and then lower themselves back down.";i:27;s:100:"Have them perform 5-6 repetitions quickly rest briefly and then do 1-2 more sets of 5-6 repetitions.";i:28;s:83:"Group exercise and movement is a crucial staple of a well-rounded activity program.";i:29;s:173:"It offers the opportunity for residents to move intentionally working on fine and large motor skills as well as improving strength flexibility endurance and range of motion.";i:30;s:26:"Articles Exercise 5140 18.";i:31;s:128:"You might think of this as an exercise of the shoulders and upper back but you can get those abdominal muscles involved as well.";i:32;s:86:"Sit up straight and a bit forward and tighten your abdominal muscles for back support.";i:33;s:68:"Hold your arms out in front of you with your elbows bent 90 degrees.";i:34;s:100:"An important part of every senior residents overall health routine should involve physical exercise.";i:35;s:84:"Here are 26 exercises for senior wheelchair users in your assisted living community.";i:36;s:104:"To help us learn why this is important the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention provides a report.";i:37;s:65:"Moving your core or torso also helps move energy around the body.";i:38;s:84:"Waken yourself up and feel more alive by moving like a tiger or a snake for example.";i:39;s:56:"All you have to do is sit in a chair and move your body.";i:40;s:78:"Depending on the images you use your sense of humour gets a great workout too.";i:41;s:102:"Senior Exercise Ideas for Activity Directors Senior fitness Senior activities Nursing home activities.";i:42;s:82:"Feb 6 2016 - Seniors need to keep active for the health of their bodies and minds.";i:43;s:81:"Here are some ideas for activity directors to keep the group active and involved.";i:44;s:24:"The best core exercises.";i:45;s:180:"A much better approach to strengthening your core is working several core muscle groups at the same time just the way you would naturally if you were lifting something or climbing.";i:46;s:64:"For older adults Boehm recommends three exercises in particular.";i:47;s:23:"Anyone can do a bridge.";i:48;s:139:"Whether theyre sitting or standing they can still get the health and mood benefits especially from seated exercises or chair yoga routines.";i:49;s:137:"There are also exercise routines that can be done using a walker for stability or just focused on the feet and ankles to reduce swelling.";i:50;s:106:"Feb 14 2020 - Explore Kathy Whites board Wheelchair Games for Seniors followed by 115 people on Pinterest.";i:51;s:69:"See more ideas about recreation therapy senior activities activities.";i:52;s:121:"Chair Exercises for Seniors Front Arm Raises Begin seated holding a ball in both hands with your palms facing each other.";i:53;s:87:"Extend your arms forward so the ball rests on your legs with your elbows slightly bent.";i:54;s:121:"Slowly raise your arms to lift the ball to shoulder level then lower back down taking about 3 seconds to raise and lower.";}}